  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Right now (in master, which is cef2d325ee1be894e883d63013f75cfac5cb1246 at the time of writing), if you implementing the scale subresource for a CRD, you have to point `labelSelectorPath` to a field under the CRD's `.status` field\r\n(see the documentation for that field, plus https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/cef2d325ee1be894e883d63013f75cfac5cb1246/staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apis/apiextensions/validation/validation.go#L511)\r\n\r\nThis restriction doesn't make a ton of sense for objects that use labelSelector as part of their spec to discover the objects that they own (e.g. ReplicaSet), and contridicts the way labelSelector works for built-in objects (e.g. for ReplicaSets, it points at `.spec.labelSelector`).\r\n\r\nWe should remove this restriction.\r\n\r\ncc @kubernetes/sig-api-machinery-bugs  @nikhita \r\n\r\n/kind bug",
  "closed_at": "2019-05-28T08:02:17Z",
